        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(cli): add --file option to image generate command",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`openclaw infer image generate` cannot accept input/reference images via `--file`, making it impossible to use CLI workflows for image-conditioned generation (brand marks, style references, product shots). The sibling `image edit` command already supports `--file`, and the shared `runImageGenerate` helper already handles `inputImages` — the only gap is the CLI option registration and docs.\n\n## Summary\n\n- **Base branch:** `main`\n- **What changed and why:** Added `--file <path>` as an optional flag to `openclaw infer image generate`, matching the existing `image edit` command shape. The `file` parameter is threaded through to the existing `runImageGenerate` helper which already supports `inputImages` when files are provided. Updated `docs/cli/infer.md` to reflect the new option.\n- **Scope boundary:** Changes `image generate` CLI registration, a colocated forwarding test, and the infer CLI docs. Does not change `image edit`, `image describe`, any image provider logic, or the `runImageGenerate` helper.\n- **Blast radius:** CLI surface only. When `--file` is not supplied, behavior is unchanged (text-only generation). When the provider does not support input images, `runImageGenerate` surfaces the capability error.\n- **Linked issue(s):** Closes #91734\n\n## Validation Evidence (required)\n\n```bash\nnode_modules/.bin/vitest run src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts\n# 98 passed; 0 failed\n```\n\n- **Commands run and tail output:** All 98 tests pass including the new forwarding test and the updated capability inspect test.\n- **Beyond CI — what did you manually verify:** Before-and-after proof using Commander registration, plus forwarding test proves `--file` → `inputImages` path end-to-end.\n- **If any command was intentionally skipped, why:** N/A\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Before (main): image generate has no --file\n\n```\n$ node --import tsx --no-warnings -e \"\nimport { Command } from 'commander';\nimport { registerCapabilityCli } from './src/cli/capability-cli.ts';\nconst program = new Command();\nregisterCapabilityCli(program, { getRuntimeConfig: () => ({}) } as any);\nconst generateCmd = program.commands.find(c => c.name() === 'infer')?.commands.find(c => c.name() === 'image')?.commands.find(c => c.name() === 'generate');\nconsole.log('Has --file:', generateCmd.options.map(o => o.flags).some(f => f.includes('--file')));\n\"\nHas --file: false\n```\n\n### After (this branch): image generate exposes --file, forwards to inputImages\n\n```\n$ node --import tsx --no-warnings -e \"\nimport { Command } from 'commander';\nimport { registerCapabilityCli } from './src/cli/capability-cli.ts';\nconst program = new Command();\nregisterCapabilityCli(program, { getRuntimeConfig: () => ({}) } as any);\nconst generateCmd = program.commands.find(c => c.name() === 'infer')?.commands.find(c => c.name() === 'image')?.commands.find(c => c.name() === 'generate');\nconst fileOpt = generateCmd.options.find(o => o.flags.includes('--file'));\nconsole.log('--file option:', fileOpt.flags);\nconsole.log('--file description:', fileOpt.description);\nconsole.log('--file is optional (not required):', !fileOpt.required);\n\"\n--file option: --file <path>\n--file description: Input file\n--file is optional (not required): true\n```\n\n### Forwarding test coverage (vitest)\n\nThe new test `forwards --file input images through image generate to inputImages` creates a real 1x1 PNG temp file, invokes `image generate --file <path>`, and asserts that the `generateImage` mock receives `inputImages` with the correct `fileName` and `mimeType` — proving the `--file` → `inputImages` forwarding path works end-to-end, matching the existing `image edit` test pattern.\n\n```\n$ node_modules/.bin/vitest run src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | grep \"forwards --file\"\n✓ capability cli > forwards --file input images through image generate to inputImages\n```\n\n### What was not tested\n\nLive image generation with a provider that supports input images (requires API credentials). The `runImageGenerate` helper path for file loading was already covered by the existing `image edit` flow and the new forwarding test.\n\n## Security & Privacy Impact (required)\n\n- New permissions, capabilities, or file system access scope? **No** — reuses the same `readInputFiles` / `detectMime` path as `image edit`\n- New external network calls? **No**\n- Secrets / tokens / credentials handling changed? **No**\n- PII, real identities, or personal data in diff, tests, fixtures, or docs? **No**\n\n## Compatibility (required)\n\n- Backward compatible? **Yes** — `--file` is optional, default behavior unchanged\n- Config / env / CLI surface changed? **Yes** — new `--file` option on `image generate`\n- If `Yes` to either: No upgrade steps needed. The option is additive only.\n\n## Rollback (required for `risk: medium` and `risk: high`)\n\nN/A — zero-risk additive CLI option.",
